quran[12]{c,v,t}:
  19,65,—the Lord of the heavens and the earth and whatever is between them. So worship Him and be steadfast in His worship. Do you know anyone who could be His namesake?’
  19,66,"Man says, ‘What? Shall I be brought forth alive [from the grave], when I have been dead?’"
  19,67,Does not man remember that We created him before when he was nothing
  19,68,"By your Lord, We will surely gather them with the devils; then We will surely bring them up around hell [scrambling] on their knees"
  19,69,Then from every group We shall draw whichever of them was more defiant towards the All-beneficent
  19,70,Then surely We will know best those who deserve most to enter it
  19,71,"There is none of you but will come to it: a [matter that is a] decided certainty with your Lord"
  19,72,"Then We will deliver those who are Godwary, and leave the wrongdoers in it, fallen on their knees"
  19,73,"When Our manifest signs are recited to them, the faithless say to the faithful, ‘Which of the two groups is superior in station and better with respect to company?’"
  19,74,"How many a generation We have destroyed before them, who were superior in furnishings and appearance"
  19,75,"Say, ‘Whoever abides in error, the All-beneficent shall prolong his respite until they sight what they have been promised: either punishment, or the Hour.’ Then they will know whose position is worse, and whose host is weaker"
  19,76,"Allah enhances in guidance those who are [rightly] guided, and lasting righteous deeds are better with your Lord in reward, and better at the return [to Allah]"